material.mattext: A certain nebula is enclosing a roughly spherical area with volume of `a`×1057 cm3, and there are 1000 hydrogen atoms per cm3. How many stars like our Sun could be formed from this nebula? Note, our Sun is composed of 1.00×1057 hydrogen atoms.

A certain star in the night sky has an absolute magnitude of +`m`. How many times brighter is this star than our Sun? 
Note, the magnitude of our Sun is +4.8.
Examine this image from NASA, and identify what type of structure is imaged
A galaxy other than the Milky Way
